"39:29:4" : {s: 39, a: 29, w: 4, r: "رجل", t: "رَّجُلًۭا", l: "رَجُل", lc: 29, tl: "rajulan", lb: "একজন মানুষ",e: "a man", b: "একজন লোক", i: "seorang laki-laki", f: 1, rm: "to go on foot, urge with foot, walk, tie by the feet, let (a female) suckle her young, be curly (hair), set free with his mother. rajjala - to comfort anyone, comb the hair, grant a respite. tarajjala - to go down without rope. rijlatun - vigour in walking. rijlun - foot, soldiers, good walker, tramp. arajil - hunters, pedestrian. rajulun - male human being, man, a person with heir. rajilun - foot, footmen (slow walkers). rijlain - two feet. arjul (pl.) - feet."},
