"39:29:6" : {s: 39, a: 29, w: 6, r: "شرك", t: "شُرَكَآءُ", l: "شَرِيك", lc: 40, tl: "shurakāu", lb: "অংশীদার",e: "partners", b: "অংশীদার হবে", i: "berserikat", f: 4, rm: "to be a companion, be sharer/partner. shirkun - share, participation, polytheism, idolatry, making associate/partner with Allah. shariik (pl. shurakaa) - associate, partner, sharer. Nouns of the second declension when followed by the affixed pronouns take the three inflexions thus shurakaa, shurakaai, shurakaaa. shaarak (vb. 3) - to share with. ashraka (vb. 4) - to make a sharer or associate, give companions (e.g. to God), be a polytheist or idolater. ashraktumuuni - you associated me as partner. mushrik - one who gives associate to God, polytheist. mushtarikun (vb. 8) - one who partakes or shares."},
"39:29:7" : {s: 39, a: 29, w: 7, r: "شكس", t: "مُتَشَٰكِسُونَ", l: "مُتَشَٰكِسُون", lc: 1, tl: "mutashākisūna", lb: "ঝগড়া করা",e: "quarreling", b: "ঝগড়াটে, পরস্পর বিরুদ্ধভাবাপন্ন", i: "dalam perselisihan", f: 1, rm: "to be perverse, stubborn, cross-tempered. Tashaakasa - to wrangle, quarrel. Mutashakisun - quarreling, at variance with each other."},
