"39:29:9" : {s: 39, a: 29, w: 9, r: "سلم", t: "سَلَمًۭا", l: "سَلَم", lc: 5, tl: "salaman", lb: "শান্তি",e: "(belonging) exclusively", b: "শুধু, মালিকানাধীন", i: "selamat (penuh)", f: 1, rm: ""},
"39:29:10" : {s: 39, a: 29, w: 10, r: "رجل", t: "لِّرَجُلٍ", l: "رَجُل", lc: 29, tl: "lirajulin", lb: "একজন মানুষ",e: "to one man", b: "এক  ব্যক্তির", i: "kepunyaan seorang laki-laki", f: 1, rm: "to go on foot, urge with foot, walk, tie by the feet, let (a female) suckle her young, be curly (hair), set free with his mother. rajjala - to comfort anyone, comb the hair, grant a respite. tarajjala - to go down without rope. rijlatun - vigour in walking. rijlun - foot, soldiers, good walker, tramp. arajil - hunters, pedestrian. rajulun - male human being, man, a person with heir. rajilun - foot, footmen (slow walkers). rijlain - two feet. arjul (pl.) - feet."},
